nodes.text: Felucia birds were a type of bird that lived on the planet Felucia. In 19 BBY, several flew by forces of the 327th Star Corps during the Battle of Felucia, and one of these birds flew near Clone Commander CC-5052 and other clone troopers as they fired on Jedi General Aayla Secura.

Felucia birds first appeared in the 2005 prequel trilogy film, Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith. They were first identified in the current canon in the video "Every Creature in the Star Wars Movies", which was released by the Star Wars Kids Youtube channel in 2019.
